China announced that it would reduce import tariffs on 1,585 tax items from November 1, 2018.
Since the beginning of this year, China has taken the initiative to reduce import tariffs.
On May 1 this year, the comprehensive tax reduction of drugs will include all general drugs for anti-cancer drugs and alkaloids with anti-cancer effects, and the import tariffs on Chinese medicine that have actual imports are zero.
At the same time, it has also greatly reduced the value-added tax burden of anti-cancer drug production and import links.
On July 1, tax was reduced on 218 tax items for cars and parts.
After the tax reduction, China's automobile tax rate has been lower than the average of developing countries, in line with the actual situation of China's automobile industry.
This tax reduction will promote the adjustment of the industry structure and the optimization of resource allocation, accelerate the survival of the fittest, help improve the quality of products and services, and is expected to promote the adjustment of automobile prices to a certain extent, so that consumers can get more benefits.
Taxes on daily consumer goods for 1,449 tax items on July 1.
Tax reduction of daily consumer goods is closely related to the people's needs for a better life.
The tax reduction is not only a large number but also a strong one, with an average tax reduction of 56%.
Tax reduction of daily consumer goods directly benefits the majority of consumers and promotes the improvement of domestic industry competitiveness.
On November 1, tax reduction will be implemented for industrial products such as mechanical and electrical equipment, parts and raw materials for 1,585 tax items.
Appropriately reducing the import tariffs on some domestic urgently needed industrial products can attract more foreign investment, which is conducive to increasing effective domestic supply and helping industrial upgrading, while helping enterprises to allocate resources on a global scale, reduce production costs, and also help reduce the pressure on the domestic environment.
According to the relevant person in charge of the Office of the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council of China, the above four independent tax reductions, and the third step of the implementation of the implementation of the results of the negotiations on the expansion of the scope of the information technology agreement on July 1 this year, will reduce the total tariff level of China from 9.8% in the previous year to 7.5%.
The overall adjusted tariff level is slightly higher than that of the EU, lower than most developing countries, and is at a moderately low level, which basically matches the status and development stage of developing countries with China.
The person in charge introduced that the overall level of tariffs, as one of the important indicators of the opening up of China's goods trade field, should be adapted to the stage of China's economic development and reflect the characteristics of the times.
China's trade in goods, the world's first, has a further opening-up economic foundation, but the quality and efficiency of trade development and developed economies are still different, so the overall level of tariffs should be appropriately reduced.
