Serbia saw Kosovo as the birthplace of the nation and the cradle of culture, as Serbia established its strongest state here in the 12th century, and the Albanians only moved in large numbers after the Ottoman invasion and the defeat of the Serbian army in the north.
The Albanians insisted that the original tribe of the Illyrians, which lived in Kosovo in the 4-5th century BC, were the ancestors of the Albanians, and therefore Kosovo has been the territory of the Albanians since ancient times.
The subjective political division has led to intense conflict between different ethnic, religious and cultural communities, resulting in intense confrontation between Serbs and Albanians in the Kosovo region.
