Kosovo became the “powder keg” of the Balkans.
In 1999, armed clashes between Albanian separatists in the Kosovo Liberation Army and the Serbian army and police led to the bombing of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, formed by Serbia and Montenegro, and the outbreak of the Kosovo War.
On 17 February 2008, Kosovo unilaterally declared its independence from Serbia.
Although there has been news that Serbia will normalize relations with Kosovo and sign a global and legally binding agreement, due to historical national grievances and geopolitical constraints, an agreement that is subject to multiple forces such as the United States, Europe and Russia has not been able to sign.
