Nearly a thousand state-owned scenic spots have lowered ticket prices by more than half of them, and the decline has exceeded 20%.
As of September 28, all localities have introduced or issued documents to the public to announce the free opening or price reduction measures of 981 scenic spots (74 free opening, 907 price reductions), Yunnan Shilin, Dali Santa, Yulong Snow Mountain, Guangxi Guilin Lijiang, Fujian Wuyi Mountain, Hunan Zhangjiajie, Shaanxi soldiers, Jiangxi Sanqing Mountain, Xinjiang Kanas and other scenic spots have implemented price reduction.
In order to implement the decision-making and deployment of the Central Economic Work Conference and the "Government Work Report", the National Development and Reform Commission issued the "Guiding Opinions on Improving the Ticket Price Formation Mechanism of State-owned Scenic Spots to Reduce Ticket Prices in Key State-owned Scenic Spots" (hereinafter referred to as the "Guiding Opinions") on June 28, requiring the improvement of the ticket price formation mechanism of state-owned scenic spots from the aspects of rationally defining the cost of ticket pricing, innovative price management methods, and strict implementation of pricing procedures to ensure that the ticket prices of high-level state-owned scenic spots are significantly effective.
All localities have actively carried out their work in accordance with the deployment requirements, and have successively reduced the ticket prices of a number of key state-owned scenic spots.
As of September 28, all localities have issued or issued documents to the public to announce 981 scenic spots free of charge or price reduction measures (free opening 74, price reduction of 907), of which 159 5A scenic spots, 4A scenic spots 534, a total of 693, accounting for 70.6%.
Among the 907 scenic spots that cut prices, 491 fell by more than 20%, accounting for 54.3%, and 214 fell by more than 30%, accounting for 23.6%.
Yunnan, Shandong, Guangxi, Shaanxi and other provinces have a large number of price-cutting scenic spots, of which the number of price-cutting scenic spots in Yunnan is more than 100, and the overall decline is more than 30%.
Anhui, Chongqing and other eight provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) government pricing 5A-level scenic spots all to achieve price reduction.
The high degree of social attention of Yunnan Shilin, Dali Santa, Yulong Snow Mountain, Guangxi Guilin Lijiang, Fujian Wuyi Mountain, Hunan Zhangjiajie, Shaanxi soldiers, Jiangxi Sanqingshan, Xinjiang Kanas and other scenic spots have implemented price cuts.
The gradual return of ticket prices to reasonable ranges in key state-owned scenic spots is conducive to promoting the transformation and upgrading of tourism from the ticket economy to the industrial economy, minority tourism to mass tourism, and scenic tourism to global tourism, which is conducive to forming a virtuous circle of optimized tourism supply structure and steady expansion of tourism consumption demand, and promoting the sustainable and healthy development of scenic spots and tourism.
At the same time, the National Development and Reform Commission stressed that all localities should strengthen the order of price in scenic spots, guide scenic spots to improve services, and ensure that prices are not reduced.
In addition, on the recent media reflected the decline in the ticket prices of individual scenic spots too small and the decline in reality, the National Development and Reform Commission has carried out special supervision, requiring all localities to deal with it seriously, respond to social concerns in a timely manner, and effectively implement the price reduction in place.
The CCPIT carries out short-, medium- and long-term optimization work in an orderly manner
The Macao Trade and Investment Promotion Bureau has submitted a short-term, long-term optimization work report on "major investment immigration" and "skilled immigrants", and at present, in addition to stepping up efforts to promote and implement the work in the report, it has also continued to listen to the opinions of the society, and continuously optimizes the content of the report and related work.
The CCPIT will introduce relevant optimization work to all sectors of society as soon as possible.
Five of them are short-term measures carried out this year; five are medium-term measures carried out in 2019; and one is a long-term measure.
In addition, the CCPIT also comprehensively reviewed the internal management system in accordance with the instructions of the Secretary for Economic and Financial Affairs, Liang Weit.
The five short-term measures carried out during the year include:
(a) Carry out review work. Prioritize the review of cases that are about to expire for seven years, the cases mentioned in the report of the CCAC, and the new renewal cases. If cases of misconduct or signs of law are found, they will be referred to the relevant judicial authorities for follow-up and treatment;
The field inspection involves the project of “major investment immigration”. By late September, more than 20 investment projects have been inspected;
A comprehensive review of the current review system. Six principles for the analysis of investment projects have been re-established in reviewing the application for "major investment immigration"; in reviewing the application for "skilled immigrants", the relevant approval mechanism will be improved by clarifying the elements conducive to the development of Macao and the conditions for priority the absorption of talents. At the same time, a list of "five industries and ten jobs" for the annual priority introduction of talents has been established to cooperate with the direction of the HKSAR Government and absorb talents more targetedly;
Increase information transparency. Including plans to gradually publish approval standards, scoring standards and proportions from the fourth quarter of this year, and further refine and publicize approval data;
In terms of improving the work of the recognition mechanism, it has been required to verify the work in Australia before confirming; major investments must be verified on site and the financial statements are submitted.
The five medium-term measures to be implemented in 2019 include:
Establish a mechanism for regular listening to the views of the Commission on Talent Development and the Economic Development Board, which was held in September with the Economic Development Committee to hold a working meeting to discuss the establishment of relevant mechanisms.
Require applicants to submit annual financial statements made by an independent third party to continuously review the operation of the investment project;
Further standardize and equivalize the process of case-by-case application and approval to reduce human error;
Comprehensively review the current staffing configuration and cooperate with the implementation of a number of optimization measures;
Step up the study of the revision of the Temporary Residence System for Investors, Managers and Specially Eligible Technicians.
As for long-term measures to intensify the study of law amendments, it is expected that the drafting of relevant laws and regulations will be carried out in the first half of 2019, and the approval criteria, review mechanism and confirmation mechanism for temporary residence permits will be further clarified, and the investigation functions of the CCPIT will be increased to more accurately approve and supervise applications for temporary residence permits.
Experts from the national filmless cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities walked into the test field to listen to the presentation of the representative of the academician team of Yu Shuxun of the Chinese Academy of Engineering.
Xinzhong network Xinjiang Shaya September 30th (Geng Dandan Wang Xiaojun) is located in Shaya County, Xinjiang filmless cotton planting test base, filmless cotton growth is happy, compared with the next to the membrane cotton "no less", a cluster of snow-white cotton competing "open", hanging branches.
From September 27 to 28, the national filmless cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
The reporter learned at the observation meeting that the filmless cotton technology system with "Chong Cotton 619" and its supporting cultivation measures as the main body has initially achieved the goal of filmless cultivation of cotton fields, reducing the pollution of the ecological environment and raw cotton of the residual film of cotton fields in Xinjiang, and making significant progress in the comprehensive technical research and demonstration of filmless cotton.
Academician Yu Shuxun, academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering, famous cotton genetic breeder, and chief scientist of the cotton system of the national modern agricultural industry technology system, introduced the growth of filmless cotton to Zhou Guomo, party secretary of Zhejiang Agricultural and Forestry University.
"Our research and development of filmless cotton comprehensive technology can fully realize the cultivation of cotton without film, can completely solve the problem of residual film pollution, to achieve green cotton."
Academician Yu Shuxun of the Chinese Academy of Engineering introduced.
Xinjiang is the most important cotton-producing area in China. According to the National Bureau of Statistics, the cotton planting area in Xinjiang in 2017 was 35 million mu, accounting for 61% of the country's cotton area.
Since the introduction of the film to China in 1982, the film cover area of various types of crops in Xinjiang has reached more than 50 million mu, and the annual use of the membrane is about 300,000 tons.
Among them, the coverage rate of cotton film reached 100%, and cotton laminating accounted for about 60% of the amount of film used in Xinjiang.
Membraneless cotton for measurement and production, cotton production can be achieved per mu of 320 kg to 350 kg.
With the increasing amount of land film investment in Xinjiang, the recovery rate of the residual film is low, the amount of residual film in the soil is gradually increased, and a series of problems such as the destruction of the soil structure caused by the residual membrane have seriously affected the sustainable development of agriculture.
The residual film not only causes serious pollution to the soil, but also has a great impact on the quality of cotton fiber.
At present, more than one-third of the cotton fields in Xinjiang have achieved mechanized harvesting.
In 2017, Xinjiang's organic cotton picking area was about 14 million mu.
The crushing film in the cotton harvest process, which is dupled in the raw cotton, is difficult to remove during the processing of raw cotton, and cannot be completely removed during subsequent textile processing, which seriously affects the quality of textile products.
On September 28, the national filmless cotton on-site observation and discussion and exchange activities were held in Shaya County, Xinjiang.
In order to focus on solving the pollution of cotton field membranes, simplifying cotton planting technology, and improving the efficiency of cotton fields, Yu Shuxun led his team to implement the "Chondom 619" filmless cotton technology planting in 8 years, adding wings to the green development of Xinjiang's agriculture.
Yu Shuxun introduced, through innovative breeding new ideas, cultivate the early, salt-resistant, low-temperature, abundant production of the new line of land cotton "Chongmin 619".
"'Contam 619' in the southern region of Xinjiang filmless cultivation conditions, to achieve membrane-free sowing machinery supporting, sowing depth improvement, no membrane under the conditions of the dripping pipe shallow burial, suitable sowing density screening, reasonable chemical regulation and a series of supporting measures."
At present, Aksu, Kurle, Aral and other places have established filmless cotton demonstration bases, with a yield of 4,800 kg per hectare.
The cultivation of cotton without film has achieved abundant production, cost savings, environmental protection, and improved comprehensive benefits.
Zhang Donghai, an agronomist of the Third Division of the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, said that through the research and demonstration of filmless cotton cultivation technology in the past six years, the yield of filmless cotton seed cotton can fully achieve a yield of 320 kg to 350 kg per mu, and may even be higher.
"Membrane-free cotton cultivation technology has great prospects."
Zhang Donghai believes that at present, filmless cotton cultivation technology can completely solve the problem of soil residual film pollution, but there is still a certain gap in economic benefits compared to membrane cultivation.
"Cotton purchase price support will be conducive to future promotion."
Yu Shuxun said that in the next step, he and his team will continue to conduct in-depth research and large-scale promotion and application of filmless cotton, make the filmless cotton industry bigger and stronger, and completely solve the problem of soil pollution caused by the membrane.
