The reporter learned from the Ministry of Finance on the 30th that the Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of Taxation, the National Development and Reform Commission, and the Ministry of Commerce recently jointly issued a notice to further encourage foreign investors to invest in China and distribute profits from foreign investors from domestic resident enterprises in China, and to use domestic direct investment to temporarily levy the scope of application of the income tax policy, and expand from foreign investment incentive projects to all non-prohibited foreign investment projects and areas.
This policy has been implemented since 1 January 2018.
The notice clearly states that foreign investors make direct investments by profit by sharing, including equity investment behaviors such as capital increases, new construction, and equity acquisitions carried out by foreign investors by profit by sharing profits, but does not include new, transferred, or acquired shares of listed companies other than eligible strategic investments.
Where a foreign investor may, in accordance with the provisions, enjoy the temporary non-collection of the withholding income tax policy but is not actually entitled, he may apply for recovery and enjoyment of the policy within three years from the date of actual payment of the relevant tax, and refund the tax paid.
Not only that, after the foreign investor enjoys the prescribed temporary non-collection of the advance income tax policy, the reorganization of the invested enterprise meets the special restructuring conditions, and the actual tax treatment in accordance with the special reorganization, can continue to enjoy the temporary non-collection of the advance income tax policy.
In order to ensure that the profits received by foreign investors are actually used for direct investment, the notice stipulates that the profits of foreign investors for direct investment are paid in cash, the relevant funds are directly transferred from the account of the profit-distributing enterprise to the account of the invested enterprise or the equity transferor, and shall not be turned around in other accounts at home and abroad before direct investment; the profits of foreign investors for direct investment are paid in real, securities and other non-cash forms, and the ownership of the relevant assets shall be transferred directly from the profit distribution enterprise to the invested enterprise or equity transfer.
The notice also requires the tax department to strengthen follow-up management according to law.
Foreign investors have enjoyed the temporary non-leviation of the income tax policy, after the subsequent management of the tax department to verify that does not meet the requirements, in addition to being the responsibility of the profit distribution enterprise, deemed to be foreign investors in accordance with the provisions of the declaration of corporate income tax, will be investigated in accordance with the law for delay in tax liability, tax delay payment period from the date of payment of the relevant profits calculated.
The U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) said on Friday it would no longer allow imports of raw materials made by China's Huahai Pharmaceuticals and those made from the company's APIs.
A drug previously produced by Huahai Pharmaceutical was recalled for containing potentially carcinogens.
The European Medicines Agency said it was considering further action on other ingredients produced by the drug company.
The FDA said that major production process problems were found during the FDA inspection of Huahai Pharmaceutical's pharmaceutical companies, and then stopped imports.
The FDA also said that it will be banned from import until Huahai Pharmaceuticals finds how the above impurities are generated and improves its quality control system.
Huahai Pharmaceutical issued a statement on the company's website on September 29, saying: "For the problems in the official inspection of the United States and Europe, the company is making rectification with a positive attitude and strong measures; for the official treatment and treatment of the US and Europe, the company is very surprised and regrettable.
In the current complex market environment, the company is worried about this.
At present, the company is organizing teams, including professional lawyers, to communicate and file complaints in accordance with relevant procedures and official communications between the United States and the European Union, so as to restore production as soon as possible.
