On June 5, the Chinese insurance IPO application passed the press conference.
As of December 31, 2017, the Ministry of Finance held 70.47% of the total share capital of China Insurance and 10.2% of the Social Security Foundation.
After the Chinese people are guaranteed to issue shares in A-shares, the shareholding ratio of the Ministry of Finance will be diluted to 63.58%, and the shareholding ratio of the Social Security Foundation will be 9.2%.
