Xinhua News Agency, Fuzhou, October 1 (Reporter Yi Xiao'an) On October 1, the "Fujian Province High-speed Railway Safety Management Regulations" was officially implemented.
The regulations put forward that within 500 meters of each side of the wire of the high-speed rail power line, it is forbidden to fly air drift objects such as kites, balloons, porous lights, and aircraft and small aircraft.
On the basis of the upper laws such as the Railway Law of the People's Republic of China and the Regulations on Railway Safety Management, according to the geographical and climatic characteristics of Fujian Province, supplementary provisions are made on the prohibition and restriction of acts affecting the safety of high-speed rail, regulating the construction and construction of high-speed rail, tree planting and other acts along the high-speed rail, further clarifying the subject and scope of supervision of high-speed rail supervision, and clarifying the responsibilities and legal responsibilities of law enforcement supervision.
The provisions for Fujian Province coastal wind, high-speed rail along the light construction materials and light drift materials are blown into the high-speed rail to affect the safety of the situation, the provisions of the high-speed rail power line wire on both sides of the range of 500 meters, prohibit the release of kites, balloons, pore lights, power umbrellas, aircraft and other airborne objects and small aircraft.
In addition, plastic greenhouses, color steel plates, sunshade nets and other lightweight objects and light floats such as low-altitude floats and plastic protective films generated during construction along the high-speed rail line, all people or users should take reinforcement protective measures to prevent the safety of high-speed railways.
In view of the characteristics of Fujian Province in the hill zone and high-speed railway tunnel, it is stipulated that within 200 meters of the central line above the high-speed rail tunnel, the construction of mountain ponds, reservoirs, levees, excavation of rivers, dry canals, wells and other acts that may affect the safety of the tunnel, railway construction units or railway transport enterprises should be solicited for opinions of railway construction units or railway transport enterprises.
At the same time, those who violate the relevant responsibilities of the Provisions will be ordered by the public security organ to make corrections; if the circumstances are more serious, the unit shall be fined not less than 5,000 yuan but not more than 10,000 yuan, and a fine of not less than 200 yuan but not more than 500 yuan for the individual; if the circumstances are serious, the unit shall be fined not less than 10,000 yuan but not more than 30,000 yuan, and a fine of not less than 500 yuan but not more than 1,000 yuan for the individual.
Where losses are caused, liability shall be borne in accordance with the law.
It is understood that with the rapid development of railway construction, the high-speed railway mileage of 200 kilometers per hour and above in Fujian Province has now reached 1516 kilometers, realizing the city-to-city train, and it is expected that the railway lines with a speed of 200 kilometers per hour and above in Fujian will reach 2,150 kilometers in the next five years.
The implementation of this provision will regulate the safety management of high-speed rail in Fujian Province, further implement the responsibilities of local government departments, coordinate railways and local forces, work together to ensure high-speed rail safety, and improve the high-speed rail safety prevention and control system in Fujian Province.
