Guangdong Province Confirms One Case of Human Infection with H5N6 Avian Influenza
The Health Bureau said that according to the latest notification from the mainland health department, a case of H5N6 avian influenza has been confirmed in Guangdong Province.
The Health Department urged residents to avoid contact with birds and to pay attention to personal and food hygiene.
According to the data, the patient is a 22-year-old man, now living in Baiyun District of Guangzhou, Guangdong Province; on September 25, he developed symptoms such as fever, was admitted to the hospital for treatment on September 26, and is currently in isolation in the hospital for treatment and in critical condition.
The patient was killed and eaten before the onset of the disease.
Since April 2014, there have been confirmed cases of H5N6 avian influenza in Sichuan, Guangdong, Yunnan, Hubei, Hunan, Anhui and Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
The Health Bureau will continue to maintain close contact with the national and neighboring health departments and the World Health Organization, and closely monitor the epidemic in various places and in Macao.
In order to prevent human infection with avian influenza, the Health Bureau calls on the public to pay attention to the following matters:
Avoid contact with birds or their secretions and excreta; if there is contact, wash your hands immediately;
Do not buy or carry unquarantined birds;
Do not eat uncompromised poultry meat, internal organs, blood products and eggs;
Pay attention to personal hygiene and wash your hands frequently;
If there are symptoms such as fever, cough, and difficulty breathing, you should wear a mask, seek medical attention as soon as possible, and detail the travel history and animal contact history to the doctor.
