Fuzhou, September 30 (Reporter Long Min) The sixth meeting of the Standing Committee of the 13th National People's Congress of Fujian Province voted on the 30th to adopt the "Regulations on Promoting the Construction of Ecological Civilization in Fujian Province".
"Green water and green mountains are Jinshan Yinshan" was written into the legislation of Fujian Province for the first time, throughout the entire regulations, and become an operable and enforceable provision.
Fujian is China's first national ecological civilization test area.
The person in charge of the Legal Affairs Office of the Fujian Provincial People's Government said that it is necessary and urgent to form a basic law on the construction of ecological civilization from the whole and the overall situation to solve the problem of regulating the construction of ecological civilization by relying on scattered rules and regulations and policy documents alone, and also provide a legal basis for formulating and issuing relevant regulations, normative documents and measures.
The regulations fully reflect the characteristics of Fujian, the ecological civilization construction practice of mature experience practice into the form of laws and regulations to promote the implementation: such as Fujian soil and water conservation management work formed a replicable, can be promoted "Changting experience", the regulations on Fujian Province, water and soil conservation management experience summary and upgrading, the provisions of the county level and above the local people's government should strengthen the unified leadership of water and soil conservation work, according to the results of the results of soil erosion to delineate the water and soil erosion key prevention areas and governance areas;Long-term system, the implementation of river and lake management and care subjects, responsibilities and funds.
The regulations stipulate that the system of lifelong accountability for ecological environment damage shall be implemented.
Those who violate the requirements of scientific development and cause serious damage to ecological environment resources shall be held accountable for the main leading cadres and relevant responsible persons who have leadership responsibilities.
According to reports, the "Fujian Province Ecological Civilization Construction Promotion Regulations" will be implemented on November 1 this year.
China and Pakistan agree to complete the construction of the Economic Corridor in a timely manner and accelerate the construction of Gwadar Port
China’s foreign ministry said on Sunday that China and Pakistan had agreed to further consolidate and expand economic ties between the two countries.
China and Pakistan issued a joint statement on Sunday to further strengthen the strategic partnership.
The two sides reaffirmed their commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor and "oppose the negative publicity against the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor."
Reuters quoted China's foreign ministry as saying that China and Pakistan will "strengthen practical cooperation in the field of trade and investment, and enhance Pakistan's industrial capacity by establishing joint ventures in priority areas, transferring labor-intensive industries, and carrying out cooperation among small and medium-sized enterprises."
According to a press release published on the website of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, the two sides agreed to complete the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor construction project in a timely manner, accelerate the construction of ports and supporting projects in Gwadar Port, focus on economic and social development, create jobs and improve people's livelihood, and accelerate cooperation in the fields of industry and parks and agriculture.
"The two sides agreed to complete the second phase of the China-Pakistan FTA negotiations as soon as possible, and continue to promote the negotiation of the China-Pakistan Trade in Services Agreement."
In a joint statement signed on Sunday, the two sides reaffirmed their commitment to the construction of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor and agreed that the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor is a win-win cooperation plan that will promote regional connectivity and bring prosperity and development to the entire region.
The two sides agreed that Gwadar Port is an important node for cross-regional connectivity and a pillar of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor.
The two sides agreed to accelerate the construction of the port and supporting projects of Gwadar Port.
China and Pakistan also said in a joint statement that they oppose negative propaganda against the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor.
The two sides agreed to establish a strategic dialogue between China and Pakistan's foreign ministers and adjust the original strategic dialogue at the deputy foreign minister level to diplomatic consultations.
In addition, the two countries will further strengthen defense cooperation and maintain high-level visits between the two militaries and exchanges between various departments and levels.
In order to further encourage foreign investors to invest in China, the Ministry of Finance of China and other four ministries and commissions jointly notified that since January 1, 2018, the profits distributed by foreign investors from domestic resident enterprises in China have been used for domestic direct investment to temporarily levy the scope of application of the income tax policy, and the foreign investment encouragement projects have been expanded to all non-prohibited foreign investment projects and areas.
According to the relevant notice published on the website of the Ministry of Finance, foreign investors must meet several conditions at the same time, including direct investment by foreign investors in terms of profit, including equity investment behaviors such as capital increase, new construction, and equity acquisition by foreign investors by sharing profits, but does not include the addition, transfer, and acquisition of shares of listed companies (except for qualified strategic investment).
The profits also derived by foreign investors belong to the dividends, dividends and other equity investment income formed by the actual distribution of retained income by Chinese resident enterprises to investors.
And the profits of foreign investors for direct investment are paid in cash, the relevant funds are transferred directly from the account of the profit-distributed enterprise to the account of the invested enterprise or the equity transferor, and may not be turned around in other accounts at home and abroad before direct investment; the profits of foreign investors for direct investment are paid in kind, securities and other non-cash forms, and the ownership of related assets is transferred directly from the profit distribution enterprise to the invested enterprise or equity transfer party, and may not be held or temporarily held by other enterprises or individuals before direct investment.
The notice also said that foreign investors through equity transfer, repurchase, liquidation and other means of the actual recovery of the temporary non-levered of the advance income tax policy treatment of direct investment, in the actual collection of the corresponding funds within 7 days, in accordance with the prescribed procedures to the tax authorities to declare the tax payment deferred tax.
In order to encourage foreign investors to continue to invest and operate in China, four ministries and commissions such as the Ministry of Finance and the Ministry of Commerce of China jointly issued a notice at the end of 2017, from January 1, 2017, direct investment in incentive investment projects for the profits distributed by foreign investors from domestic resident enterprises in China, and if they meet the prescribed conditions, implement a deferred tax policy and temporarily do not levy advance income tax.
The executive meeting of the State Council of China decided last week to further strengthen the protection of intellectual property rights by extending the scope of application of foreign reinvestment from the introduction of advance income tax on encouraging foreign investment projects to all non-prohibited projects and areas.
The reporter learned from the National Health Commission that compared with decades ago, the incidence of malnutrition among children and adolescents in China has decreased, and the incidence of overweight and obesity has increased significantly.
Experts pointed out in this regard, maintain a healthy weight, the most important concept is to "cure the disease", vigorously promote scientific fitness, reasonable diet.
According to the "China Youth Health Education Core Information and Interpretation (2018 Edition)" recently released by the National Health and Health Commission, the key to maintaining a healthy weight is a reasonable diet and scientific exercise.
Being overweight, obese, and losing weight blindly are not good for health.
The health risks behind the "little fat pier" cannot be ignored.
Ding Gangqiang, director of the Nutrition and Health Institute of the China Center for Disease Control and Prevention, said that overweight obesity endangers the normal growth and development of adolescents, and has adverse effects on their psychology, behavior, cognition and intelligence, and even leads to high blood pressure, high blood sugar and high blood lipids in children.
At the same time, overweight and obesity in adolescents are easy to continue into adulthood, which will increase the risk of chronic diseases such as hypertension and diabetes in adolescents.
Ding Gangqiang said that from 2010 to 2012, the nutrition and health status of Chinese residents showed that the overweight rate of children and adolescents aged 6-17 in China was 9.6%, the obesity rate was 6.4%, and the two were 16%.
At the same time, overweight and obese children and adolescents show that boys are higher than girls and urban areas are higher than rural characteristics, and the rate of overweight obesity has increased significantly in recent decades.
How do teenagers cope with overweight obesity?
Zhang Li, deputy director of the Scientific Fitness and Health Promotion Research Center of the State Administration of Sports, pointed out that the main reason for obesity among adolescents is excessive calorie intake and insufficient physical activity.
For this simple obesity, we should pay attention to scientific exercise plus reasonable diet control.
Zhang pointed out that the most important concept to maintain a healthy weight is to "cure the disease", which is a very important part of the school, parents and students to carry out a full range of popular science education, popularize the dangers of overweight and obesity, improve the awareness of young people's prevention.
Adolescents should regularly undergo physical examinations, monitor growth and development indicators such as height and weight, and detect and scientifically determine whether overweight and obesity occur early, so as to take timely interventions.
For adolescents who are already overweight and obese, Ding Gangqiang suggested that in addition to actively scientifically arranging meals and exercise, adolescents are in a special physiological stage, and should avoid using hunger or semi-hungry therapy to control and lose weight, and should not blindly take weight loss drugs.
Sept 28 (Reuters) - Facebook (FB.O) said on Friday that hackers had stolen digital landing codes, giving them access to nearly 50 million user accounts, in the face of unprecedented faces, the worst security breach it ever had.
Facebook, which has more than 2.2 billion monthly users, said it had not yet determined whether the attackers misused any accounts or stolen personal information.
The company also did not find the location of the hackers, and it was not sure if the hackers targeted specific victims.
Initial analysis revealed that it was a large-scale attack.
CEO Mark Zuckerberg called the incident "really serious" in a media conference call.
A company spokesman said his account and the account of Chief Operating Officer Sheryl Sandberg were also affected.
Facebook shares fell 2.6 percent on Friday, dragging down Wall Street's main stock index.
U.S. lawmakers said Friday that the attack could increase calls for data privacy legislation.
“This is another sad piece of evidence that Congress needs to take action to protect the privacy and security of social media users,” Democratic Senator Mark Warner said in a statement.
Federal Trade Commission Commissioner Rohit Chopra said on Twitter that I wanted to get answers to Reuters’ reports of the security breach.
