China News Agency Yichang October 1 (Guo Xiaoying Liu Min) the newly revised "Three Gorges - Gezhouba water conservancy hub navigation dispatching procedures" (hereinafter referred to as the "dispatching procedures") officially began on October 1st, the Three Gorges lift aircraft in the trial and opening of two years, officially with the locks unified dispatch.
On the first day of the implementation of the new regulations, the waters of the Three Gorges-Gezhouba were in good order.
The Three Gorges Navigation Authority of the Yangtze River issued its first security inspection plan at 21:00 on September 30, and carried out security inspection on 160 ships, with a total of 124 ships passing security checks.
At 14:00 on October 1, the navigation department arranged the first floodgate plan after the implementation of the new regulations.
After the implementation of the new regulations, the security inspection plan is issued once a day at 9 o'clock and 21:00, and the over-daming plan is issued once a day at 14:00 and 20 o'clock, so that the ship can flexibly arrange the dam plan.
The "dispatching regulations" add the "classification control" of the ship over the dam scheduling principle, according to the lock and lift machine function positioning to clarify the priority of the dam ship, the gate of the short-term passenger ship adjusted to the same priority level as the demonstration ship and the integrity ship.
This is also two years after the test operation of the lift, the official and the lock unified dispatch.
The Sichuan River and the Three Gorges Reservoir District large long and wide demonstration ship, new energy power ship also for the first time among the priority level.
At the same time, the "dispatching regulations" will be "navigable dispatching management waters" from the previous 180 kilometers of near dam waters adjusted to Yunyang Yangtze River Bridge to Shijingjiang Bridge 541.8 km of water, and divided "core waters, near dam waters, control waters, dispatching waters".
This is conducive to the ship party to choose the appropriate water to wait for the gate, reduce the backlog of ships waiting for the gate in the dam area.
The "Dispatch Regulations" also put forward good faith constraints such as canceling the declaration of ships with violations and delaying the dam for 24 hours according to the characteristics of the current ship crossing and waiting gate.
After the Three Gorges water storage, the navigation conditions in the reservoir area have been improved, which has promoted the rapid development of Yangtze River shipping.
Data show that the annual volume of goods passing by the Three Gorges locks and Gezhouba locks increased from 34.3 million tons in 2004 to 138 million tons and 140 million tons in 2017, respectively.
In the past two years, the Three Gorges Ascending aircraft has passed 5,767 ships, 162,200 passengers, and transported 1.712 million tons of freight.
Chen Dongyuan, deputy director of the Three Gorges Navigation Authority, said that the "dispatching regulations" have a positive effect on promoting the management of integrity over the gate, maintaining the navigation order of the two dam hubs, dredging the pressure on ships waiting for the gate in the dam area, and improving the navigation ability.
