With the approval of Premier Li Keqiang, the State Council recently issued the Decision on Further Reducing the Catalogue for the Management of Production Licenses for Industrial Products and Simplifying the Approval Procedures.
The "Decision" proposes to further reduce the production license management catalogue of industrial products, cancel the production license management of 14 types of industrial products, and delegate the authority for the management of the production license of four types of industrial products to the quality and technical supervision department of the people's government at the provincial level.
After this reform, the implementation of industrial product production license management products, from last year's 38 categories of pressure to the current 24 categories.
The "Decision" clearly stipulates that the simplified approval process is implemented for products in the catalogue.
The first is to change the product inspection before the issuance of the certificate by the issuing authority organization to the product inspection and qualification report issued by the qualified inspection and testing institution submitted by the enterprise at the time of application.
Second, in addition to hazardous chemicals, the provincial people's government quality and technical supervision department (market supervision and management department) to implement the license of the product on-site review, the enterprise submitted the application and product inspection pass report and made a commitment to ensure product quality and safety, after the form of review qualified can receive the production license, and then within the prescribed time to accept on-site review.
Third, the enterprise production and operation catalogue of different categories of products, in accordance with the principle of "one enterprise, one certificate", when applying for a new license or applying for a renewal license, and review and issue a license.
The "Decision" requires all regions and relevant departments to solidly promote the reduction of catalogues and the simplification of approval procedures.
Strengthen the commitment of enterprises to publicize and post-on-site review, strengthen credit supervision and restraint means, implement the main responsibility of enterprise quality, and revoke the production license if false commitments and non-compliance with requirements are met.
For products that cancel the production license management of industrial products, it is necessary to effectively strengthen post-event supervision, involving public health and safety, environmental protection and other products can be converted to mandatory certification, make a positive list and publicize to the public, unify certification standards, reasonably reduce and certify the testing project, and the mandatory certification costs are in principle borne by the financial system at all levels.
Take support measures to encourage enterprises to carry out voluntary certification, and promote the establishment of brands and expand the market.
It is necessary to benchmark international advanced standards and promote the improvement of industrial product quality.
Give full play to the role of third-party social organizations to ensure the quality and safety of industrial products.
For products that retain the production license management of industrial products, it is necessary to improve the standard system, give full play to the advantages of industry supervision, strengthen the responsibility of "who approves and supervises", dynamically assess product quality and safety risks, reduce the catalogue in a timely manner, delegate the approval authority or convert it to certification management.
In September, China's comprehensive PMI increased month-on-month, and the manufacturing PMI fell month-on-month.
According to data released by the National Bureau of Statistics of China on the 30th, in September, China's comprehensive PMI output index was 54.1%, higher than the previous month and the average annual value of 0.3 and 0.1 percentage points, indicating that the overall production and business activities of Chinese enterprises remained stable.
In the same month, the manufacturing production index and the non-manufacturing business activity index, which constituted the composite PMI output index, were 53.0% and 54.9% respectively, down one liter from the previous month.
Among them, China's manufacturing PMI was 50.8%, down 0.5 percentage points from the previous month.
Zhao Qinghe said that this month's manufacturing PMI mainly has five characteristics:
First, the manufacturing fundamentals are generally stable.
Among the 21 industries surveyed, the PMI of 14 industries is in the expansion range, of which the manufacturing PMI of medicine, special equipment, electrical machinery and equipment is located at a higher operating level of more than 53.5%, with a faster growth rate.
The second is the small fluctuations in supply and demand.
The production index and the new order index were 53.0% and 52.0 percent, down 0.3 and 0.2 percentage points from the previous month, respectively, and supply and demand continued to maintain a state of prosperity, but the expansion slowed down slightly.
The new export orders index and import index were 48.0% and 48.5%, respectively, lower than the previous month's 1.4 and 0.6 percentage points, the prosperity fell to the lowest level in the year.
Fourth, the cost of raw material procurement by enterprises has increased.
The main raw material purchase price index was 59.8%, up 1.1 percentage points from the previous month, and the ex-factory price index was 54.3%, the same as the previous month, all of which were the highest in the year.
Fifth, the operation of large enterprises is stable, and the operating conditions of small enterprises continue to improve.
Large enterprise PMI was 52.1%, the same as last month, the index has been in the expansion range of 52.0% and above this year, and this month's production index and new orders index have increased month-on-month, is the main driving force for the manufacturing industry to maintain expansion; medium-sized enterprises PMI was 48.7%, lower than the previous month's 1.7 percentage points, in the contraction range; small business PMI was 50.4%, higher than the previous month 0.4 percentage points, rising for two consecutive months.
In the same month, China's non-manufacturing business activity index was 54.9%, up 0.7 percentage points from the previous month, and rebounded for two consecutive months.
Zhao Qinghe believes that the non-manufacturing industry in general continues to maintain a steady and good development momentum.
The business activity index of road transportation, securities, real estate and other industries continues to be below the critical point, and the total business volume has decreased.
Nagoya, Nov 5 (Reuters) - Bank of Japan Governor Haruhida Toyan said on Monday that the central bank was aware that long-term ultra-loose monetary policy could squeeze the profit margins of financial institutions and could destabilize the country’s banking system.
But he said that given the low inflation and uncertainty in overseas economies, the Bank of Japan needed to maintain its massive stimulus package while keeping a close eye on the pros and cons of its policies.
“The Bank of Japan fully acknowledges that the strength of financial institutions will be increasingly affected by continued monetary easing,” Kuroda said in a speech to business leaders in Nagoya.
He said that if financial institutions are more active in taking risks to make up for the impact of narrowing profit margins caused by low interest rates over the years, the banking system is likely to be volatile in the event of a serious negative impact.
"Although these risks are not large at present, the central bank will pay close attention to the development of the situation and encourage financial institutions to take necessary measures," he said.
Minutes of the Bank of Japan meeting, released earlier on Monday, showed that at the September meeting, the Bank of Japan’s policy committee discussed the rising cost of long-term easing.
Minutes of the meeting showed that one member said that if the economy continues to expand, "the BOJ will have more flexibility in policy in the future."
According to the minutes, another member said that given the limitations of the policy period, the committee should discuss how long the Bank of Japan can maintain stimulus policies.
Kuroda said the Bank of Japan would assess the financial risks posed by easing, while also considering uncertainty surrounding Japan's economic prospects, as Sino-U.S. trade frictions and rising protectionism could affect global demand.
“The impact of such problems on the Japanese economy is limited for the time being,” Kuroda said.
"But how the problem continues, the impact on the Japanese economy is likely to become larger," he added.
“There is a need for sustained and strong monetary easing, while considering both positive and negative effects in a balanced way,” said Kurada.
Despite the growing ills of the aggressive stimulus package, such as the long-term low interest rates eroding the profits of financial institutions, low inflation has forced the Bank of Japan to maintain the plan.
The Bank of Japan maintained monetary policy last month; in the face of the risks posed by the global trade war dispute, Kuroda ruled out the possibility of a recent rate hike.
June 1, 2018, the United States Cardiff, Tesla electric car on the corporate logo.
Under a settlement, U.S. Tesla and its chief executive, Musk, have agreed to pay a $20 million fine each to financial regulators, and Musk will step down as chairman of the company but remain CEO.
The settlement will bring Tesla’s turmoil to an end for two months.
The SEC’s disclosure on Saturday of the securities fraud charges settlement agreement will take investors to the fore.
Investors had been concerned that a protracted legal battle would only hit the still-lost electric car company further.
The SEC sued Musk for fraud on Thursday, saying its Aug. 7 tweet misled investors.
The tweet said he was considering taking Tesla private for $420 a share and had secured funding.
The SEC said the tweets were actually unfounded and that the market turmoil it caused hurt investors.
Investors and corporate governance experts say the deal could bolster Tesla, which has been hit hard by Musk’s recent behavior.
Steven Heim, head of Boston Common Asset Management, said the settlement should put Musk under more oversight while not taking the “devastating” step of driving him out of Tesla.
The asset manager owns shares of Tesla’s battery maker Panasonic.
Under the proposed agreement, Tesla must appoint an independent chairman, two independent directors, and a board of directors to develop controls on Musk’s external communications.
"The matter was resolved quickly and in the best interests of our markets and our investors, including Tesla shareholders, on agreed terms," SEC Chairman Clayton said in a statement.
Thursday’s allegations caused Tesla’s market value to evaporate about $7 billion, and the company’s market cap was $45.2 billion on Friday, down from General Motors’ $47.5 billion.
The SEC withdrew its request to take Musk off the company’s top position in the settlement.
Many investors say the penalty would be catastrophic.
“I think it’s the best possible outcome for all involved,” said Ivan Feinseth of Tigress Financial Partners, who gave Tesla a “neutral” rating and called the SEC’s penalty a “light penalty” for Musk.
"He's still CEO for Tesla."
Neither Musk nor Tesla acknowledged or denied the SEC’s allegations in the settlement, nor did they immediately respond to requests for comment.
The settlement agreement still needs to be approved by the court.
