The official said that this is only the statistics of the city of Palu, the capital of Central Sulawesi Province, and does not include the Dongala County and nearby Sigi areas, where the epicenter is located, because communications in these two areas are still interrupted and no reports of the number of people killed have been received.
Because many roads in the city of Palu have been severely damaged, heavy machinery is difficult to access, and search and rescue efforts have encountered great difficulties.
In order to ensure rescue, the Palu airport, which began to close on the evening of the 28th, suspended all commercial flights after reopening on the evening of the 29th, and the reporter had completed the flight from Jakarta to Palu that night.
After the earthquake and tsunami, the Chinese Embassy in Indonesia learned about and verified the situation of Chinese citizens in the disaster area through various channels.
So far, no reports of Chinese casualties have been received.
