The newly revised personal income tax law adjusts the judgment standard for Chinese personal income tax residents from one year to 183 days.
The relevant person in charge of the Ministry of Finance and the State Administration of Taxation said on the 30th that in order to maintain policy stability, the next step in implementing the new personal income tax law, we will consider continuing to make preferential arrangements for overseas people, including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
The person in charge said that the implementation regulations of the current personal income tax law have special preferential provisions on the taxation of foreign people, and individuals who have no residence in China but have lived for more than one year and less than five years, who derive their income from outside China may only pay personal income tax on part of the payment of units or individuals in China.
The part paid abroad does not require the payment of personal income tax in China.
China's Ministry of Finance, the State Administration of Taxation, the National Development and Reform Commission, and the Ministry of Commerce also issued a notice to expand the scope of application of the policy of foreign investors not to levy advance income tax on direct investment by distributing profits.
The profits distributed by foreign investors from domestic resident enterprises in China are used for domestic direct investment to temporarily not collect the scope of application of the advice income tax policy, and the foreign investment encouragement projects are expanded to all non-prohibited foreign investment projects and areas.
During the 73rd session of the United Nations General Assembly, some positive messages were released around the Korean Peninsula issue.
South Korean President Moon Jae-in relayed North Korea’s “irreversible” nuclear denuclearization and said U.S. President Donald Trump and North Korea’s supreme leader, Kim Jong Un, could meet by the end of the year.
The U.S. State Department later said Secretary of State Mike Pompeo would visit North Korea in October to push for the implementation of the commitments made by U.S. and North Korean leaders to meet in Singapore.
Since the beginning of this year, the DPRK and the Roka have broken the ice to open the road of dialogue, the leaders of the DPRK and the ROK and the United States have held a meeting, the general trend of de-escalation on the Korean Peninsula has continued, and the principle of resolving the Korean Peninsula issue has been upheld.
First of all, the essence of the Korean Peninsula issue is a security issue has not changed, and the key to achieving peace on the Peninsula is to properly and balance the legitimate security concerns of all parties, rather than blindly exerting pressure on each other and emphasizing their own demands.
Second, in the dialogue on realizing the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula, the parties concerned still have differences on the steps and ways to achieve the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. Due to the long-term lack of political trust between the DPRK and the United States, the game thinking of "who comes first and who after" is still strong.
At the Security Council's open meeting on the Korean Peninsula held at the United Nations Headquarters in New York, all parties issued different voices on the issue of sanctions against the DPRK, once again highlighting the two points on the Korean Peninsula issue.
U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo has insisted that sanctions on North Korea will not be lifted until the Korean Peninsula is completely denuclearized.
Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov, for his part, stressed the principle of "response by action", noting that "the weakening trend of sanctions should be the same as the steps taken by North Korea on the road of gradual denuclearisation."
There is no doubt that all relevant parties should continue to implement the DPRK-related resolutions in a comprehensive, complete and accurate manner, but the pressure is not the purpose, and the implementation of sanctions and the promotion of a political solution are the requirements of the Security Council resolutions.
As Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi said, in view of the current positive developments in inter-Korean and US-US relations, China believes that it is necessary for the Security Council to consider the timely launch of reversible clauses, so as to encourage the DPRK and all relevant parties to take greater steps towards denuclearization.
Looking back on the past, the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and every progress in the peace process require sufficient political courage from all parties.
At present, in the face of the international community's expectation of promoting the political settlement of the Korean Peninsula issue, all relevant parties should especially show political strength, make political decisions, implement commitments, resolve difficult problems, continue to take steps to the contrary, advance the process of denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and establish a peace mechanism on the Peninsula in parallel, and jointly create a permanent peace on the Peninsula.
The People's Government of Ji County, Linfen City, Shanxi Province, came to the news on the 1st that during the National Day, the Yellow River Jukou Waterfall scenic spot in the county will maintain a relatively high water level and does not have open conditions.
In order to ensure safety, the scenic spot was temporarily closed during the National Day.
The Yellow River pot mouth waterfall is the second largest waterfall in China and the largest yellow waterfall in the world.
The Yellow River runs here, the stone walls on both sides stand, and the mouth of the river is narrow as a pot, forming the spirit of "a pot of the Yellow River in a thousand miles".
According to the reporter's understanding, each year from June to October is the Yellow River flood season, from July 12, 2018, due to the high water level of the Yellow River, Shanxi Yellow River pot mouth scenic spot began to close one after another, so the closure of the pot mouth scenic spot has been nearly a month.
Ni Yufeng, chief engineer of the Jukou Scenic Area Management Committee, told the media that this is the longest duration of the high water level of the Yellow River in the past 20 years, "it has not been so long before, the closure time of our flood season in 2017 is 4 days, and this year is nearly a month."
It is understood that the Shanxi Yellow River Hukou waterfall scenic spot was originally in order to meet the "Eleven" Golden Week, but also in advance of the increase in personnel arrangements and vehicle maintenance, and even temporary staff recruitment has been in place.
According to the "Notice on Doing a Good Job in the Yellow River Flood Prevention Work during the National Day" issued by the "Yellow River Flood Prevention and Drought Control Headquarters Office", it is required to do a good job in the flood control work of the Yellow River during the National Day.
At present, the flow of the Yellow River's dry river is large, the flow of the upstream river is maintained at 2,000-3000 cubic meters per second, the flow of the middle river is maintained at 2,500-3,500 cubic meters per second, and the downstream river flow is maintained at a level of 3,000 cubic meters per second.
Health centres and health posts provide influenza vaccination services during special National Day holidays
The Health Bureau has ordered 150,000 doses of the 2018-2019 quadrivalent influenza vaccine this year, giving priority to free vaccinations for high-risk people at this stage, and providing vaccination services from 9 a.m. to 1 noon in order to facilitate the vaccination of residents during the holidays, health centers and health stations under the Health Bureau, especially on the National Day holiday (October 1 and 2) from 9 a.m. to 1 noon.
In addition to the above-mentioned convenience measures, the health centers and health stations under the Health Bureau have been launched from the plan, and the influenza vaccination service time from Monday to Friday has been extended to 8 p.m., and as of 4 p.m. on September 30, 4,158 people have been vaccinated, compared with more than 3,714 people in the same period last year.
Free vaccinations include the following Macao residents: persons aged 6 months to 18 years, persons aged 50 and above, pregnant women, all chronically ill persons, including obese persons (i.e. persons with a body mass index of BMI of 30 or above), as well as staff in institutions, nurseries, kindergartens, primary schools, secondary schools, all health workers, and Macao residents working in casinos.
At the same time, the Health Bureau believes that other personnel who have been vaccinated, including the public sector, will take the initiative to contact the relevant agencies to obtain the list and arrange for vaccination by the health center.
In order to facilitate the vaccination of vaccinators and reduce the waiting time for the province, the Health Bureau will send medical staff to the local secondary school, primary school, kindergarten and nursery during the period from October to December this year to carry out collective influenza vaccination for young children, primary and secondary school students, teachers and employees; in addition, the Health Bureau will also arrange for people to be vaccinated by the elderly and disabled institutions, public departments or other institutions with a large number of people.
Students and young children who are unable to participate in the collective vaccination can be vaccinated at the vaccination station or health center of the Count Ren General Hospital from December 3, 2018 with the Macao Resident Identity Card, the Health Bureau User Card, the influenza vaccination card (if any), the student card, the employee card or the occupation certificate document.
The Health Bureau reminds residents that between September 2017 and August 2018, people who have been vaccinated against influenza from 2017 to 2018 will still need to be vaccinated for the new season of influenza vaccine from September 2018, because the influenza antigen component contained in the 2018-2019 Northern Hemisphere influenza vaccine has been updated, targeting the winter of 2018-2019 and the seasonal influenza in the summer of 2019.
The peak flu period in Macao is generally from January to March each year, and it is later than in temperate areas (such as northern China and Japan), and the Health Bureau calls on the elderly, children, pregnant women, obese people and chronically ill people who are more likely to have complications and those who are often in contact with high-risk people should be vaccinated as soon as possible.
