After 6 years, Tencent welcomes the adjustment of major organizational structure, it is clear that it will not lay off employees.
On the 30th, Tencent announced the official launch of a new round of overall strategic upgrading, the organizational structure ushered in a new round of optimization and adjustment after a lapse of 6 years, and the reorganization and integration on the basis of the original seven business groups (BG) were six, and the adjustment did not involve layoffs.
The new six business groups.
After six years, two new business groups appeared.
It is understood that the new business group not only maintains the advantages and characteristics of the vertical field, retaining the original enterprise development business group (CDG), interactive entertainment business group (IEG), technology engineering business group (TEG), WeChat business group (WXG); but also highlights the integration effect, the new cloud and intelligent industry business group (CSIG), platform and content business group (PCG).
