The sinking of an illegal migrant boat in the Aegean Sea of Turkey killed five people.
ISTANBUL, Sept. 30 (Xinhua) -- According to Turkish media reports on the 30th, an inflatable boat carrying illegal immigrants capsized in the Aegean Sea of Turkey on the same day, killing at least five people.
The report said that the inflatable boat, which was scheduled to go to an island in Greece, sank near the Enez area in the northwestern Turkish province of Edirne on the same day, and the reason for the sinking was unknown.
At present, it is not clear the number of illegal immigrants on the sinking inflatable ship.
Due to estimates that people are still trapped in the sea, the relevant search and rescue operations are still continuing.
The Aegean Sea was the first route for illegal immigrants to cross the continent through Turkey.
After Turkey controlled it under an agreement signed with the EU in March 2016, the number of people smuggled through this channel was greatly reduced.
But this year, the number of people smuggling on this channel has rebounded.
