From November 1st, China will reduce the most-favoured nation tax rate for some goods, and the total tariff level will be reduced to 7.5%.
According to the decision of the 26th executive meeting of the State Council, the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council issued a notice on the 30th to reduce the most-favoured nation tax rate for some goods from November 1, 2018.
According to the "Announcement of the Customs Tariff Commission of the State Council on Reducing Import Tariffs on Some Goods", in order to adapt to industrial upgrading, reduce the cost of enterprises and meet the needs of the masses at multiple levels of consumption, from November 1 this year, the most-favoured-nation tax rate for some industrial goods and other goods will be reduced.
Tax reduction goods a total of 1585 items, accounting for about 19% of the total number of tax items in China, the average tax rate from 10.5% to 7.8%, the average decline of 26%.
The tax reduction mainly involves textiles; stone, ceramics, glass products; some steel and base metal products; mechanical and electrical equipment and parts, such as metal processing machinery, textile machinery, construction machinery, power transmission and transformation equipment, electrical equipment, instrumentation, etc.; resource commodities and primary processing products, such as non-metallic minerals, inorganic chemicals, wood and paper products, gemstones, etc.
At the same time, with the reduction of the total tariff level, especially the import tariffs on drugs and consumer goods, the tax rate of import duties on imported goods has been reduced accordingly.
In order to implement the decision-making and deployment of the Party Central Committee and the State Council, China has implemented zero tariffs on the vast majority of imported drugs since May 1 this year, reduced the import tariffs on automobiles and parts and some consumer goods from July 1, and implemented the third step of the information technology agreement to expand the products.
The reporter learned from the State Council Tariff Policy Committee that since this year, after many consecutive independent adjustments, the total level of tariffs in China will be reduced from 9.8% last year to 7.5%, with an average reduction of 23%.
Properly reducing tariffs is conducive to promoting the balanced development of foreign trade and promoting a higher level of opening up, and it is also conducive to the overall utilization of international and domestic resources and promoting the structural reform of the domestic supply side.
The relevant person in charge of the committee said that this year is the 40th anniversary of reform and opening up, and the active reduction of the overall level of tariffs is to implement the practical action of General Secretary Xi Jinping's important speech at the Boao Forum for Asia, and it is also an important measure for China to further expand opening up and actively expand imports according to its own high-quality development needs.
