The first joint inspection of the Han River into the sea in the DPRK in 65 years
The South Korean Ministry of National Defense confirmed on the 5th that the ROK and the DPRK launched a joint inspection of the Han River and the Linjin River into the sea mouth waters on the same day.
The initiative is in preparation for ensuring the freedom of navigation of civilian vessels on both sides.
According to a briefing provided to the media by the South Korean Ministry of National Defense on the same day, this is the first joint inspection of the Han River into the sea since the signing of the Korean War Armistice Agreement in 1953.
The ROK signed a military agreement in September this year, and agreed to jointly visit the Han River into the sea and other waters from November to ensure the protection of the waters in the future, development and tourism.
In October, the ROK and the DPRK planned a joint waters visit at a general-level meeting.
On November 5, the joint inspection of inter-Korean waters was officially launched.
The joint delegation consists of 20 people, including the inter-Korean military and experts.
According to the South Korean Ministry of National Defense, during this visit, personnel on both sides did not carry weapons and banned the use of words and deeds that stimulated each other.
"Because there is no military demarcation line near the mouth of the sea, the area was once a surprisingly high-incidence area, but through joint inspection, it will become a new peaceful area in the future."
The waters of the joint inspection between the two Koreas are about 70 kilometers long and have a total area of about 280 square kilometers.
According to the South Korean Ministry of National Defense, the South Korean side will send six research ships to detect the depth of the seawater and provide basic information for the safe navigation of the waters; after the completion of the investigation, the navigation map will be provided for the traffic of civilian ships.
The two Koreas held a summit meeting in Pyongyang in October 2007 to reach an agreement on the joint use of the Han River and the Linjin River into the sea, but the follow-up negotiations were stranded due to tensions on the peninsula.
According to the military agreement signed by the Ronder and the Democratic People's Republic of Korea in September, in the future, the ships of the two sides need to inform each other in advance before sailing in common waters.
According to the website of the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia on the 4th, recently, Chinese citizens Guo Yuqin and Mao Runxin lost contact during tourism in Mongolia.
It is understood that the two are members of the blue sky rescue team, on October 19, the two contacted their relatives and friends in China, saying that they would immediately enter the mountain expedition near Lake Kusugul, and shared their location through WeChat, after which they lost contact and suspected to have gone to the no-man's land.
The Chinese Embassy in Mongolia has always attached great importance to protecting the legitimate rights and security of Chinese citizens in Mongolia, and attached great importance to consular protection and assistance.
After learning the news that the above two tourists lost contact, the embassy immediately launched the emergency plan for the protection of the insurance, and strived to seize the golden rescue time and work hard.
The Embassy maintains close communication with the families of the parties concerned, assists the family in immediately reporting the case to the Mongolian police, and provides the family with a list of interpreters for selection.
The embassy first met with the heads of the Ministry of External Relations of Mongolia, the General Directorate of Police and the General Administration of Emergency Situations, and informed the relevant situation, asking the Mongolian side to carry out search and rescue as soon as possible, and maintain close communication with the Mongolian side throughout the search and rescue process to ensure timely grasp of the latest progress.
At the same time, the Embassy assisted the family in issuing notices in Mongolia, and widely mobilized Chinese overseas Chinese and Chinese-funded enterprises to actively participate in the search for people, providing effective clues, and providing relevant assistance to a number of blue sky rescue team members who went to Mongolia to assist in rescue.
Under the strong impetus of the embassy, the Mongolian side sent a rescue team for the first time and promised to exempt the search and rescue costs.
The General Directorate of Police and the General Directorate of Emergency Situations directed the police and emergency services of the province of Kusugur to make full efforts to search and rescue.
Because Lake Kusugur is located in the northern border with Russia in northern Mongolia, is remote, sparsely populated, traffic and communication are extremely inconvenient, and at present Mongolia has entered a severe winter, the temperature is as low as minus 20 degrees, the local police and emergency departments have overcome great difficulties, mobilized almost all the police forces, and mobilized local herdsmen, through riding, walking, visiting herders, etc., to carry out carpet search and rescue around the two lost contact positions.
At the same time, in response to the special situation of pastoral areas, Monfang has been publishing notices through the radio cycle for many days.
The relevant staff of the domestic blue sky rescue team have also come to Mongolia to actively participate in the rescue with the Mongolian side.
The safety of the two missing people has always touched our hearts.
So far, the two have lost contact for more than 10 days, the embassy has received some clues, but has not found the two, the current search and rescue operations are still in the process of intense progress.
The Embassy will always continue to pay attention to this matter in accordance with the principle of "people-oriented", promote the Mongolian side to continue to search and rescue, and provide maximum assistance to the families of the parties.
The Embassy calls on compatriots and enterprises in Mongolia, if they are informed of the relevant clues, please contact the Chinese Embassy in Mongolia at the first time.
